title: Rediscovery of the Feminine in Storytelling with Neil DeGraide
description:
I speak with musician and filmmaker Neil DeGraide about his film Queen of The Night. It is such a beautifully made film and I hope that all who watch this interview also go and check it out. We focus in on the aspects of the feminine used in his story, and contrast them with how things are done today. This was such a fun chat, and I encourage you to check out Neil's fantastic band that he and his wife are part of called @Dirt Poor Robins . They produce and perform all of the music for "Queen of the Night" as well. 

Listen to the podcast version here: https://anchor.fm/podcast-9b57fe4/episodes/Rediscovery-of-the-Feminine-in-Storytelling-with-Neil-DeGraide-e1c2l00

The first episode of Queen of the Night: https://youtu.be/X_GugZS1pqQ

Neil's band's website: https://www.dirtpoorrobins.com

follow me on twitter @andrealynnlewis
email me at andreawiththebangs@gmail.com
follow my vintage Instagram @fringevintagefinds
